   Version 2.31    Bugfixes                           September the 9th, 1993
                   Totally new volume bars

       - Returning from the DOS shell, the colors were not set, resulting
         to a really ugly screen.
       - A couple of bugs fixed in the S3M loader. Hope it works with all
         the S3Ms now. If not, please report.
       - I totally rewrote the colorbar routine. This routine now supports
         up to 16 bars (the other colors on the screen will be masked off
         as you get more bars, though), and is much faster than the
         previous one. It also supports bars starting and ending wherever
         they want, so that I made some choices for the volume bars:
         original top-bouncing ones, traditional ones that come from the
         floor, and nice ones that bounce in the middle of the screen.
         Try them by pressing B..
       - In the fading routine there was a bug. Most clearly it occured
         while the end screen was being shown: some noise was heard. Now
         fixed.

