   Version 2.30    Bugfix                             September the 2nd, 1993
                   Layout changed
                   More time for playing!
                   Power meters
                   Colors changed
                   Internet address changed

       - Bugfix: A bug in the 669 loader fixed
       - Screen layout changed a little, because
       - I wanted to have more time to calculate music. Now the bars eat
         less power, and maybe also users of slower machines can use them..
       - Power meters added. They are the little bouncing bars in the
         borders of the screen.
       - I decided to radically change the colors of the PMP. I chose blue,
         as you can see.. I hope you like the new colors. There may be
         an unchanged color somewhere (resulting as a flashing/almost
         invisible color). If you notice one, please tell it to me.
       - Because of these color changes, PMP now no longer works with EGA.
         Sorry.. anyway, no VGA check is made, so you may hear music,
         anyway.. Try!
       - I finally got a real Internet account. The address is
         jlahd@clinet.fi. Please use this instead of the old one.
       - There still is a bug in the S3M loader. For some odd reason, it
         does not load for example cant.s3m (Why can't you remember/
         Marvel of FC). I am working on it..
       - GUS support COMING SOON

