   Version 2.23    Bugfixes                                May the 24th, 1993
                   ARIA support
                   669 support

       - S3M modules now play much better (commands are better supported)
       - A bug in the STM and S3M loaders caused awful noises in modules
         with very short looping instruments. Corrected, but not tested,
         because I have no such modules.. Report if the bug is still there.
       - Memory handling in V86 environment changed slightly. If you still
         encounter runtime errors in the V86 mode, but not in the non-V86-
         more, please report.
       - PMP now supports the ARIA soundcard, though it does not work very
         well with QEMM for some STRANGE reason. Sorry about that, I'm
         trying to fix the bug..
       - PMP now knows how to load the 669 modules. It also knows how to
         play them... I guess...

