   Version 2.22    Bugfixes                                 May the 6th, 1993
                   ScreamTracker 3 support!

       - I REALLY thought I had corrected the module list window updating
         bug -- and, actually, I did. But, while correcting the bug I
         happened to create a new one with the same result: nothing was
         updated anyway.. Now definitely FIXED.
       - A bug appeared into the memory handling in some version, I don't
         know when. Anyway, it took about 30k of extra memory from DOS
         shell when running with QEMM/EMM/other memory manager. Now fixed.
       - Maybe also other bugs fixed. Too long a period between versions..
       - PMP now plays ST3-modules (*.S3M)! There are three batch files
         included to rip the music from Future Crew's demos Unreal, The
         Party'93 -intro and Panic.

