   Version 2.01    Bugfixes                               March the 5th, 1993
                   New module format

       - A bug in module loader caused some patterns to black out from the
         loaded module. Corrected.
       - Problems with corrupted modules solved; previously they just caused
         a memory-low -message to be shown, now they are handled correctly.
       - The system is made a bit more stabile with some fixes. I hope it
         helps somebody.. (It's not easy to write a DOS-shelling protected
         mode application..)
       - PMP is having problems with some disk caches. The system locks up
         when you try to load something in the DOS shell. If somebody has
         suggestions for solving this problem, please contact me.
       - New AMF format with over four channels supported

